node.text:
~may 31, 2019~
today is the last day of mental health awareness month and i just want to give a quick shoutout 
to everyone who battles with mental illness 
to anyone who wakes up each morning wishing they didn’t and fighting through the day
to everyone who has gotten help
to everyone who hasn’t brushed their hair in days cause they’re too depressed to do a damn thing
to everyone who’s grades are as low as they are
to everyone who is trying their hardest to make it through the day
to everyone who has needed to distract themself from one pain and focus on another
to anyone has taken or attempted to take their life
to everyone who has trauma
to everyone who is too anxious to get out of the car
to everyone who’s dark imagination comes alive
to everyone who is bullied and walks the halls everyday, facing the one who makes you feel like you don’t belong 
to everyone who rips themself apart every time they look in the mirror 
to everyone who has been broken so severely that nothing helps
to those whose compulsions take over themselves and they now feel as though they are their OCD
to everyone who is struggling
to my babies from McLean SE who are the most inspirational people i know
to my best friends for sticking with me and fighting by my side
to my family who has done everything they can to help me heal
to my entire professional support system
to ms grace carolyn didemonico
to all of you, 
you are strong
you are loved
you are beautiful 
you are intelligent
you are worth it
you are not alone
you are so incredibly loved 
keep fighting because life is beautiful. it may not seem that way now, but i promise you’ll get there. time to prove your strength to your demons and show them how badass you are. time to see brighter days and to show the world the brightest smile anyone’s ever seen.
every new day is a blessing. 
i believe in you, stay strong💛
#mentalhealthawareness #anxiety #depression #suicideprevention #suicideawarness #selfharm #ocd #ptsd #ptsdawareness #staystrong #mcleansoutheast #schizophrenia #paranoia #iloveyou #metoo
So proud of you 🥰🙏 you got this
You are strong, loved, beautiful, intelligent, worth it, and not alone as well! Healing is possible
@lexcb i love you so incredibly much 💛😭
@samanthach2018 thank u! remember im always here for you :)
Proud of you keep it up I needed to read this today ❤️
♥️ Love you and love this! You should be proud ♥️
@sarahreed11 @caitlinmonica love you beautiful ladies. ur both so strong💛
ur so cute. i love u
strongest girl ever💕 love you girl!
@ellenabou i love u so much mom. thank you for everything. u r my world💛

We love you so much and are so proud of how far you’ve come!! Each day is a struggle, but just know that we are always here for you and what may seem unbearable today, will be in the past tomorrow!! You are stronger than you know!! Keep fighting the good fight!! Love your dandelions!!!💛💛💛
Strongest girl I know! Love u Claudia💛💛💛

We’re fighting suicide one piece of clothing at a time. Our vision is to build a community of people who are constantly talking to people around them about suicide awareness. We want you to join us in fighting the darkness of suicide.
I am so proud of how far you’ve come ❤️❤️❤️ I love you so much

how’d i fall in love with you so fast? my #1. 
i love you so <3
we were destined to meet, i swear. thank you, god 💛💛💛
@gracecdidomenico i love you so incredibly much and i’m truly blessed to have been able to meet u and be absolute rebels in the outcoves💛💛
